				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">heres...<a name="18575"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 2 04 6:10 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Heres my experience;
<br />

<br />
During my first ever MB raid, the spider groups wiped about a minuite before the MB died. So a monk, a very talented monk continued to run around, fd, and run around with these spiders ever spawning on him. Eventually the pack looked like it had 50 in it. The monk finally died and the spiders killed the rest of the raid during rezz efforts. Loot rotted, about 7 people were flagged, out of 50 or so. 
<br />

<br />
So keeping them busy isnt an option.
<br />

<br />
Spider spawn is fairly quick. This means these bards have to keep the continuious spawn of spiders dead. If bards were &quot;good&quot; enough, they could get down a system where they were to swarmkyte or something. But if two bards crossed paths while attempting this in the somewhat narrow halls of the MB room area, its a wipe.
<br />

<br />
My point?
<br />

<br />
Bards controlling EVERY spider corner is rediculious unless you have four tallented bards, maybe more incase one dies or something. And then your going to want some for the MB effort itself.
<br />

<br />
Ive personally done this spider kyting thing. And yes, if your shorthanded on members and you want to attempt, a bard can be the answer. But it takes skill and adaptation.
<br />

<br />
Then again, most guilds worth there nametag can drop the MB in 30 seconds anyway. Its the pickups that use this stratagy in the end.</span></td>
