			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: PoI MB encounter: kiting the spiders<a name="20318"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 10 04 2:58 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I encountered two good stragities to the MB encounter:
<br />

<br />
First, find 4 good enchanters. These enchanters will watch the spiders, mezz all of them, and pray that none of the mezzes break. After the MB dies, people run back, and start to help the enchanters out. There are three problems with this: the enchanter can mess up and die, the enchanter can miss mobs, and the enchanter's mana can run out. This method has worked every time I have done it (3 times), but in one of the instances I was stuck mezzing spiders that got through. I find a good place to park yourself, as a bard, is near the door of the MB, just in case any get through. The push component of our mezz is a lifesaver here. 
<br />

<br />
Second, have a group assigned to spider killing at each corner. This is very people intensive, but if you have enough of the zerg, it will work. The problem, I have found, with this is that people don't help you, and that people form your group are forced to leave after the MB dies, to go get themselves flagged. So, in the course of 8-10 minutes after the MB dies, your group has a tendency to slowly die off, one by one. At the end of one of these, I was forced to start kiting spiders, acquired about 10, died (when a cleric intervened), and quickly saw everyone still in the MB room spawn around PoK/PoT. People did get there loot and flags though. Again, it requires a lot of people. 
<br />

<br />
I hope that helps. I don't beleive kiting the spiders is a good option, there are simply too many.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
