				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: PoI MB encounter: kiting the spiders<a name="20731"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 11 04 5:48 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well, the first successful MB kill done by my guild and our allies, we had exactly 3 enchanters.  They held 3 of the corners and the other corner was held by myself and one other bard and not one spider got away from us.  We kept the first 6 that spawned locked down with mez before we had to start kiting and by then, we only had to keep them occupied for about 20 or 30 seconds before MB was down.  Once we heard that the gnome had been pulled out of MBs room, we faded and the drama in our corner was over.
<br />

<br />
So a pair of bards can hold a corner easily.  One bard by himself would be a challenge, but I certainly think it's possible.  The spiders ARE social so normal swarm/AOE kiting tactics will work. Just use Largos and they won't leave you alone.
<br />

<br />
While Mose is giving great advice for a 72 person raid, our guild has 40 mains -- no more.  We can fill 8 groups if we bring all our two boxers.  
<br />

<br />
And we can still take out MB.</span></td>
