				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: PoI MB encounter: kiting the spiders<a name="29270"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 22 04 3:55 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>&quot;During my first ever MB raid, the spider groups wiped about a minuite before the MB died. So a monk, a very talented monk continued to run around, fd, and run around with these spiders ever spawning on him. Eventually the pack looked like it had 50 in it. The monk finally died and the spiders killed the rest of the raid during rezz efforts. Loot rotted, about 7 people were flagged, out of 50 or so. &quot;
<br />

<br />
Too bad your monk's heroic efforts were wasted. What we do when the MB drops is all run out of the room. Immediately. A monk tags the gnome to get him to the hallway where he is safe to hail. Corpse draggers watch the spiders run in and drag out quickly. Once the initial wave of formally mezzed spiders has suicided in MB's room, the rest are spaced so you can run in to loot as well. Just have to be careful and time it right. Some guilds resume spider killing to let people get in to loot, but we just let people run the guantlet.
<br />
</span></td>
