			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: PoI MB encounter: kiting the spiders<a name="67785"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 22 04 10:41 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>1)  Set up four CC groups:  Chanter, OT, druid/shaman healer.  Assign one to each corner.  OT helps chanter on resists, healer keeps team alive.  When MB is down, CC groups suicide, get dragged rezzed.  This is the safest way to go, and generally how I approach this encounter.
<br />

<br />
2)  If you are lacking enchanters set up small DPS groups to fill gaps.  One tank, one druid/shaman healer and 2-3 damage dealers.  When MB is down, these groups just stop killing any non-agro spiders.  If you have a massive surplus of people, this is the safest method.
<br />

<br />
3) I have, in a pinch, kited the spiders in one corner after the chanter that was supposed to cover it left, and in the confusion the DPS group assigned to the corner didn't understand to stay there.  You don't need to kill the spiders, you just need to keep agro on them so they don't run to MB room.  Just agro one and run around the room with the big light beam and sing a long range AE to get their attention.  Don't let anyone heal you, or buff you so when MB is down you can Fade off agro, or just suicide.  I don't think it is unreasonable to think that you could just have 4 people, one in each corner, kite the spiders while you fought MB and then suicide at the end.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
